
{{alias}}( x )
    Compute the arcsine of a number.

    The domain of `x` is restricted to `[-1,1]`. If `|x| > 1`, the function
    returns `NaN`.

    Parameters
    ----------
    x: number
        Input value.

    Returns
    -------
    y: number
        Arcsine (in radians).

    Examples
    --------
    > var v = {{alias}}( 0.0 )
    0.0
    > v = {{alias}}( {{alias:@stdlib/math/constants/float64-pi}}/2.0 )
    ~1.0
    > v = {{alias}}( -{{alias:@stdlib/math/constants/float64-pi}}/6.0 )
    ~-0.5
    > v = {{alias}}( NaN )
    NaN
